{"type":"message","id":"ec6134ca","parentId":"29300ce2","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:20:40.272Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_u6p73nr2a4le_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"FILE: pulse_2026-03-24 042019.md\r\n# Pulse: 2026-03-24 042019\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: scripts/tic_classifier.ps1 (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and decide what single concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. There's been significant synthesis work on architecture comparison, gap-decay mapping, and compression-causal duality\r\n3. The NEXT ACTION is the TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n\r\nThe pending TIC Experiment involves:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe most direct way to start the TIC experiment is to:\r\n1. Look at the existing pulse logs to understand their structure\r\n2. Start implementing the classifier\r\n\r\nLet me look at the most recent pulse log to understand the format, then create a basic TIC classifier script.\r\n\r\nFirst, I should read the most recent pulse log to understand the structure, then create a simple Python script for the TIC experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC Experiment is the next critical step for Phase 1 advancement, but I need to first examine the actual pulse log structure to design an effective classifier. The most recent pulse log is `pulse_2026-03-24 041714.md`.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nRead the recent pulse log to understand content structure, then create a basic TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier script that can analyze pulse logs for invariant patterns.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n\r\nAnalyzes pulse logs to classify content as INVARIANT (stable across sessions) vs VARIANT (changes between sessions).\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\n- Invariant content = causal structure (persists, enables prediction)\r\n- Variant content = noise/accident (ephemeral details)\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse content prediction from invariants\r\n\r\n## Approach\r\n1. Parse pulse logs for content tokens\r\n2. Compare adjacent pulse logs for changes\r\n3. Classify tokens: INVARIANT if appears in N�3 consecutive sessions\r\n4. Validate by predicting next pulse content from learned invariants\r\n\r\n## TODO\r\n- [ ] Implement log parser\r\n- [ ] Build token frequency table across sessions\r\n- [ ] Classify invariant/variant tokens (threshold: N�3)\r\n- [ ] Measure classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Test next-pulse prediction from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria\r\n\r\n---\r\n*Created: 2026-03-24 for Phase 1 TIC Experiment*\r\nfile: research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 04:20:36"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":566,"aggregated":"FILE: pulse_2026-03-24 042019.md\r\n# Pulse: 2026-03-24 042019\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: scripts/tic_classifier.ps1 (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and decide what single concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. There's been significant synthesis work on architecture comparison, gap-decay mapping, and compression-causal duality\r\n3. The NEXT ACTION is the TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n\r\nThe pending TIC Experiment involves:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe most direct way to start the TIC experiment is to:\r\n1. Look at the existing pulse logs to understand their structure\r\n2. Start implementing the classifier\r\n\r\nLet me look at the most recent pulse log to understand the format, then create a basic TIC classifier script.\r\n\r\nFirst, I should read the most recent pulse log to understand the structure, then create a simple Python script for the TIC experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC Experiment is the next critical step for Phase 1 advancement, but I need to first examine the actual pulse log structure to design an effective classifier. The most recent pulse log is `pulse_2026-03-24 041714.md`.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nRead the recent pulse log to understand content structure, then create a basic TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier script that can analyze pulse logs for invariant patterns.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n\r\nAnalyzes pulse logs to classify content as INVARIANT (stable across sessions) vs VARIANT (changes between sessions).\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\n- Invariant content = causal structure (persists, enables prediction)\r\n- Variant content = noise/accident (ephemeral details)\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse content prediction from invariants\r\n\r\n## Approach\r\n1. Parse pulse logs for content tokens\r\n2. Compare adjacent pulse logs for changes\r\n3. Classify tokens: INVARIANT if appears in N�3 consecutive sessions\r\n4. Validate by predicting next pulse content from learned invariants\r\n\r\n## TODO\r\n- [ ] Implement log parser\r\n- [ ] Build token frequency table across sessions\r\n- [ ] Classify invariant/variant tokens (threshold: N�3)\r\n- [ ] Measure classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Test next-pulse prediction from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria\r\n\r\n---\r\n*Created: 2026-03-24 for Phase 1 TIC Experiment*\r\nfile: research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 04:20:36","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774340440270}}
