{"type":"message","id":"c664e400","parentId":"67be793d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:20:47.262Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_kwxhcxsgjyj9_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 042019\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: scripts/tic_classifier.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and decide what single concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. There's been significant synthesis work on architecture comparison, gap-decay mapping, and compression-causal duality\r\n3. The NEXT ACTION is the TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n\r\nThe pending TIC Experiment involves:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe most direct way to start the TIC experiment is to:\r\n1. Look at the existing pulse logs to understand their structure\r\n2. Start implementing the classifier\r\n\r\nLet me look at the most recent pulse log to understand the format, then create a basic TIC classifier script.\r\n\r\nFirst, I should read the most recent pulse log to understand the structure, then create a simple Python script for the TIC experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC Experiment is the next critical step for Phase 1 advancement, but I need to first examine the actual pulse log structure to design an effective classifier. The most recent pulse log is `pulse_2026-03-24 041714.md`.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nRead the recent pulse log to understand content structure, then create a basic TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier script that can analyze pulse logs for invariant patterns.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n\r\nAnalyzes pulse logs to classify content as INVARIANT (stable across sessions) vs VARIANT (changes between sessions).\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\n- Invariant content = causal structure (persists, enables prediction)\r\n- Variant content = noise/accident (ephemeral details)\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse content prediction from invariants\r\n\r\n## Approach\r\n1. Parse pulse logs for content tokens\r\n2. Compare adjacent pulse logs for changes\r\n3. Classify tokens: INVARIANT if appears in N≥3 consecutive sessions\r\n4. Validate by predicting next pulse content from learned invariants\r\n\r\n## TODO\r\n- [ ] Implement log parser\r\n- [ ] Build token frequency table across sessions\r\n- [ ] Classify invariant/variant tokens (threshold: N≥3)\r\n- [ ] Measure classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Test next-pulse prediction from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria\r\n\r\n---\r\n*Created: 2026-03-24 for Phase 1 TIC Experiment*\r\nfile: research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 04:20:36\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774340447260}}
{"type":"message","id":"393ae4ce","parentId":"c664e400","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:20:50.469Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me read the pulse log that was referenced - pulse_2026-03-24 041714.md - to understand the full structure.","thinkingSignature":"0da013def26095adebe90be2f1e5defbfc63d175027319a5bdf91497218a1eea"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_540sz17ngwxx_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 041714.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3134,"output":83,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15171,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774340447262}}
{"type":"message","id":"8cc18246","parentId":"393ae4ce","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:20:50.476Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_540sz17ngwxx_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 041714\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what single action would best advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent state:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 (architecture cross-analysis) are complete\r\n- There's a key insight about COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY that needs to be tested\r\n- The NEXT ACTION is the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\r\n- Need to implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe most impactful next step would be to implement the TIC classifier on the pulse logs. This is the concrete experiment that tests the hypothesis that causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what's needed:\r\n1. Read pulse logs from `logs/pulse_*.md`\r\n2. Implement TIC classifier to identify invariants vs variants\r\n3. Measure classification accuracy\r\n4. Predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nI should implement the TIC classifier. Let me think about how to structure this:\r\n\r\nThe TIC classifier should:\r\n1. Compare pulse logs to find patterns that repeat (invariants) vs patterns that change (variants)\r\n2. Use these invariants to predict the next pulse content\r\n3. Measure accuracy against success criteria\r\n\r\nLet me implement a simple TIC experiment script that:\r\n1. Loads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies common patterns (invariants) - like \"phase\" markers, \"goals\" structure, \"action\" format\r\n3. Classifies content as invariant or variant\r\n4. Attempts to predict the next pulse\r\n5. Reports accuracy metrics\r\n\r\nI'll create a PowerShell script for this since we're in a Windows environment and using PowerShell for pulses.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant patterns across pulse logs and tests prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `scripts/tic_classifier.ps1` - a PowerShell script that implements the TIC experiment, comparing pulse logs to identify invariant structures (causal) vs variant content, then measuring classification accuracy and next-pulse prediction performance.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Tests hypothesis: Causal structure = Invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$PulseCount = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Continue\"\r\n$timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\"\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Experiment Started: $timestamp ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\n\r\n# --- Step 1: Load recent pulse logs ---\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | \r\n    Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | \r\n    Select-Object -First $PulseCount\r\n\r\nif ($pulseFiles.Count -lt 5) {\r\n    Write-Host \"Insufficient pulse logs for TIC experiment\" -ForegroundColor Red\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Loaded $($pulseFiles.Count) pulse logs\" -ForegroundColor Green\r\n\r\n# Parse each pulse into structured components\r\n$pulses = @()\r\nforeach ($file in $pulseFiles) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $file.FullName -Raw\r\n    $pulses += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        File = $file.Name\r\n        Content = $content\r\n        Lines = ($content -split \"`n\").Count\r\n        HasGoal = $content -match \"##?\\s*Goals?\"\r\n        HasAction = $content -match \"###?\\s*ACTION\"\r\n        HasMutation = $content -match \"###?\\s*MUTATION\"\r\n        HasObservation = $content -match \"###?\\s*OBSERVATION\"\r\n        Phase = if ($content -match \"Phase\\s+(\\d+)\") { $Matches[1] } else { \"0\" }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# --- Step 2: Define INVARIANT markers (causal structure) ---\r\n$invariantPatterns = @(\r\n    \"^\\#\\#?\\s*Goals?\",\r\n    \"^\\#\\#?\\s*Active\",\r\n    \"^\\#\\#?\\s*Completed\",\r\n    \"^\\#\\#?\\s*Pending\",\r\n    \"^\\#\\#?\\s*Notes\",\r\n    \"^\\#\\#?\\s*OBSERVATION\",\r\n    \"^\\#\\#?\\s*ACTION\",\r\n    \"^\\#\\#?\\s*MUTATION\",\r\n    \"^\\- \\[ \\]\",\r\n    \"^\\- \\[x\\]\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n# --- Step 3: Classify each line as INVARIANT or VARIANT ---\r\nWrite-Host \"`n--- Classification Results ---\" -ForegroundColor Yellow\r\n\r\n$totalLines = 0\r\n$invariantCount = 0\r\n$variantCount = 0\r\n$classifiedLines = @()\r\n\r\nforeach ($pulse in $pulses) {\r\n    $lines = $pulse.Content -split \"`n\"\r\n    foreach ($line in $lines) {\r\n        $totalLines++\r\n        $isInvariant = $false\r\n        \r\n        foreach ($pattern in $invariantPatterns) {\r\n            if ($line -match $pattern) {\r\n                $isInvariant = $true\r\n                break\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        if ($isInvariant) {\r\n            $invariantCount++\r\n        } else {\r\n            $variantCount++\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        $classifiedLines += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n            Pulse = $pulse.File\r\n            Line = $line.Substring(0, [Math]::Min(60, $line.Length))\r\n            Type = if ($isInvariant) { \"INVARIANT\" } else { \"VARIANT\" }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n$classificationAccuracy = if ($totalLines -gt 0) { \r\n    [Math]::Round(($invariantCount / $\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 04:17:48\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774340450474}}
