{"type":"message","id":"a39939f0","parentId":"5b78b6bf","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:21:36.825Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. The pulse log is from 04:17:14 and the current pulse ran at 04:20:19. Let me check if the research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md file was created by the mutation.","thinkingSignature":"5f498ca77d66313032f6f490e59b9d0d995b5080080fb1dd70226658b663166d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cly9opokgcq8_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Test-Path \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\research\\TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\"; if (Test-Path \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\research\\TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\") { Get-Content \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\research\\TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\" }","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":11025,"output":163,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23142,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774340493259}}
{"type":"message","id":"15a6b14b","parentId":"a39939f0","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:21:37.350Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_cly9opokgcq8_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"True\r\n# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n**Created:** 2026-03-23\r\n**Status:** READY TO RUN\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCausal structure = invariant structure. A compressor that discovers invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n## Method\r\n\r\n### Step 1: Collect Pulse Logs\r\n```powershell\r\nGet-ChildItem logs/*.md | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First 20\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Step 2: Extract Content Features\r\nFor each pulse, extract:\r\n- Topic keywords (nouns/verbs)\r\n- File references\r\n- Question marks (open problems)\r\n- Action items (verbs in imperative)\r\n\r\n### Step 3: Compute Invariants\r\nFind features that persist across multiple pulses (invariant = appears in A��?�A�3 pulses).\r\n\r\n### Step 4: Compute Variants\r\nFind features unique to single pulses or clusters (variant = appears in <3 pulses).\r\n\r\n### Step 5: Predict Next Pulse\r\nUsing invariant/variant classification, predict which features appear in pulse N+1.\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- **Classification:** >70% invariant/variant accuracy\r\n- **Prediction:** >60% next-pulse feature recall\r\n\r\n## Log Inventory\r\n| Pulse | Date | Key Content |\r\n|-------|------|-------------|\r\n| (to be populated) | | |\r\n\r\n## Results (TBD)\r\n\r\n[NEW_FILE]\r\n---\r\n# TIC Experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCausal structure IS invariant structure �?\" compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- Invariant/Variant classification accuracy: >70%\r\n- Next-pulse prediction accuracy: >60%\r\n\r\n## Data\r\n- Source: `logs/pulse_*.md` (20+ pulse logs)\r\n- Target: Last pulse is `pulse_2026-03-23 145438.md`\r\n```\r\n\r\n[NEW_FILE]\r\n---\r\n# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCausal structure IS invariant structure - compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n## Objective\r\nTest if >70% of pulse content can be classified as invariant/variant, and if invariants can predict next-pulse content with >60% accuracy.\r\n\r\n## Method\r\n1. Tokenize pulse logs into content blocks\r\n2. Classify each block as INVARIANT (appears in multiple pulses) or VARIANT (unique)\r\n3. Build invariant graph showing which blocks co-occur\r\n4. Predict next pulse from invariant sequence\r\n5. Validate against ground truth\r\n\r\n## Status\r\n- [x] Script created: `src/tic_classifier.py`\r\n- [ ] Run on last 20 pulse logs\r\n- [ ] Measure classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Measure prediction accuracy\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\n[NEW_FILE]\r\n---\r\n# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n## Phase 1 Advancement: Compression-Causal Duality Validation\r\n\r\n**Hypothesis:** Causal structure IS invariant structure �?\" compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n**Success Criteria:**\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse content prediction accuracy\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Step 1: Extract Pulse Features\r\nFrom each `logs/pulse_*.md`:\r\n- Goals mentioned (persistent vs new)\r\n- File references (repeated vs unique)\r\n- Action patterns (routine vs novel)\r\n- Insight keywords (reinforced vs first-occurrence)\r\n\r\n### Step 2: Classify Invariants\r\n- **INVARIANT:** Pattern appears in �%�3 consecutive pulses\r\n- **VARIANT:** Pattern appears in <3 pulses or changes form\r\n\r\n### Step 3: Predict Next Pulse\r\nFrom invariants in pulse N, predict:\r\n- Which goals will persist\r\n- Which files will be referenced\r\n- Which actions will repeat\r\n\r\n### Step 4: Validate\r\nCompare predictions against actual pulse N+1 content.\r\n\r\n## Implementation Status\r\n- [ ] Extract features from last 20 pulse logs\r\n- [ ] Compute invariant/variant classifications\r\n- [ ] Generate next-pulse predictions\r\n- [ ] Measure accuracy vs success criteria\r\n- [ ] Document results in `research/TIC-RESULTS.md`\r\n\r\n## Pulse Log Analysis (Last 20)\r\n```\r\n\r\n[NEW_FILE]\r\n---\r\n# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n# Phase: Phase 1 Advancement - COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n# Created: 2026-03-24\r\n# Goal: Validate that causal structure = invariant structure\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nAn LLM that can identify temporal invariants across pulse logs has discovered causal relationships.\r\nCompression that preserves invariants IS causal discovery.\r\n\r\n## Method\r\n1. Extract features from last 20 pulse logs\r\n2. Classify each feature as INVARIANT (stable across sessions) or VARIANT (changing)\r\n3. Use invariants to predict next pulse content\r\n4. Measure accuracy against success criteria\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n# See: experiments/tic_classifier.py\r\n\r\n## Pulse Log Files (n=20)\r\n- logs/pulse_2026-03-*.md\r\n\r\n## Results (to be filled)\r\n- classification_accuracy: pending\r\n- prediction_accuracy: pending\r\n- invariants_found: []\r\n- variants_found: []\r\n\r\n## Next Steps\r\n1. Run TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n2. Validate against success criteria\r\n3. If pass: Phase 1 and Phase 2 collapse into unified TIC problem\r\n4. If fail: Refine I� parameter and retry\r\n\r\n[NEW_FILE]\r\n---\r\n# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n## Hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n- **Goal**: Test if invariant/variant classification >70% and next-pulse prediction >60%\r\n- **Method**: Analyze pulse logs for recurring patterns vs unique content\r\n\r\n## Classification Criteria\r\n\r\n### Invariants (persistent across pulses)\r\n- File paths and directory structures\r\n- Core architecture decisions\r\n- Active/completed phases\r\n- Pending action items (stable across sessions)\r\n\r\n### Variants (session-specific)\r\n- Timestamps and dates\r\n- Specific numbers (counts, ratios)\r\n- Observations about current state\r\n- Newly added items\r\n\r\n## Log Analysis\r\n\r\n### Pulse log structure to extract:\r\n- Goals section (stable  invariant)\r\n- Pending actions (relatively stable  invariant)\r\n- Recent history (variant  session-specific)\r\n- Notes (mixed  need classification)\r\n\r\n## Success Metrics\r\n- [ ] >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] >60% next-pulse content prediction from invariants\r\n\r\n## Implementation Plan\r\n1. Parse last 20 pulse logs\r\n2. Extract goal/pending content\r\n3. Classify each line as invariant or variant\r\n4. Measure classification accuracy (manual validation sample)\r\n5. Predict next pulse goals from invariants\r\n6. Compare prediction to actual next pulse\r\n\r\n---\r\n*Created: 2026-03-24*\r\n*Status: IN PROGRESS*"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":520,"aggregated":"True\r\n# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n**Created:** 2026-03-23\r\n**Status:** READY TO RUN\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCausal structure = invariant structure. A compressor that discovers invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n## Method\r\n\r\n### Step 1: Collect Pulse Logs\r\n```powershell\r\nGet-ChildItem logs/*.md | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First 20\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Step 2: Extract Content Features\r\nFor each pulse, extract:\r\n- Topic keywords (nouns/verbs)\r\n- File references\r\n- Question marks (open problems)\r\n- Action items (verbs in imperative)\r\n\r\n### Step 3: Compute Invariants\r\nFind features that persist across multiple pulses (invariant = appears in A��?�A�3 pulses).\r\n\r\n### Step 4: Compute Variants\r\nFind features unique to single pulses or clusters (variant = appears in <3 pulses).\r\n\r\n### Step 5: Predict Next Pulse\r\nUsing invariant/variant classification, predict which features appear in pulse N+1.\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- **Classification:** >70% invariant/variant accuracy\r\n- **Prediction:** >60% next-pulse feature recall\r\n\r\n## Log Inventory\r\n| Pulse | Date | Key Content |\r\n|-------|------|-------------|\r\n| (to be populated) | | |\r\n\r\n## Results (TBD)\r\n\r\n[NEW_FILE]\r\n---\r\n# TIC Experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCausal structure IS invariant structure �?\" compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- Invariant/Variant classification accuracy: >70%\r\n- Next-pulse prediction accuracy: >60%\r\n\r\n## Data\r\n- Source: `logs/pulse_*.md` (20+ pulse logs)\r\n- Target: Last pulse is `pulse_2026-03-23 145438.md`\r\n```\r\n\r\n[NEW_FILE]\r\n---\r\n# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCausal structure IS invariant structure - compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n## Objective\r\nTest if >70% of pulse content can be classified as invariant/variant, and if invariants can predict next-pulse content with >60% accuracy.\r\n\r\n## Method\r\n1. Tokenize pulse logs into content blocks\r\n2. Classify each block as INVARIANT (appears in multiple pulses) or VARIANT (unique)\r\n3. Build invariant graph showing which blocks co-occur\r\n4. Predict next pulse from invariant sequence\r\n5. Validate against ground truth\r\n\r\n## Status\r\n- [x] Script created: `src/tic_classifier.py`\r\n- [ ] Run on last 20 pulse logs\r\n- [ ] Measure classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Measure prediction accuracy\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\n[NEW_FILE]\r\n---\r\n# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n## Phase 1 Advancement: Compression-Causal Duality Validation\r\n\r\n**Hypothesis:** Causal structure IS 